  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-7 clean Not-accepted)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped-out with documented rationale. Decision is Not accepted because two assessed factors — Discretization error and Output comparison — achieved levels that are marginally below the required threshold after final review, and no offset rationale is claimed. The rejection is grounded in the structured evidence and documented by the credibility assessment team.",
